This category is about Emacs menus of any kind, including menubar menus and popup menus. Click the header above to find all pages in category Menus.

* MenuBar -- How to customize menu-bar menus.
* [[MenuBarPlus|Menu Bar+]] -- Enhancements to the standard menu-bar menus.
** HelpMenuBarPlus -- Enhancements to the menu-bar '''Help''' menu.
** DiredPlus -- Enhancements to the menu-bar menus in [[DiredMode]].
* MenusAsKeymaps -- explanation of the structure of Emacs menus
* EasyMenu -- Define menus more easily.
* CreatingPopupMenus -- how to
* CreatingMenuBarMenus -- how to
* ImenuMode -- Add buffer-specific menus to the menu-bar automatically.
* MenuAccessFromKeyboard -- libraries that let you access menus from the keyboard (without the mouse), including:
** TextModeMenu (`tmm-menubar') -- Menu navigation that comes with Emacs.
** LaCarte -- Use [[completion]] and [[Icicles - Cycling Completions|cycling]] to access [[menu bar]] menu items.
** [[Icicles - Key Completion]] -- Navigate the menu hierarchy using key completion. `##[menu-bar]##' is a prefix key, just like `C-x'. Submenus are also prefix keys, and leaf menu items are command bindings. 
** CategorizingInformationManager (`ee-menubar') -- Browse the menubar as a textual tree.
** TextMenu
** IswitchMenu -- [[IswitchBuffers|Iswitchb]]-like access to menu items.
* [[Icicles - Multiple-Choice Menus]] -- Easily define commands that let users make ''multiple'' choices from menus.
* ModeLineMinorModeMenu â€“- Pop up MinorMode menus from the ModeLine.
* StickyMenus -- Menus in the X Windows version of GNU Emacs requires holding down the mouse button.
* EevMode -- writing many EmacsLisp hyperlinks constructs SEARCHABLE menu.
* OneKey -- A new keystroke help menu system.
* OneTwoThreeMenu -- Emulatin of Lotus 123 for DOS user interface
* '''Open File''' dialog box for specific systems:
** <tt>[[w32browser-dlgopen.el]]</tt> -- for Microsoft Windows (see MsShellExecute)
** MacOSTweaks -- for MacOS
* SaveAsHtml -- Additions to the '''Info''' menu for saving Info text to HTML.
